1 Taller1 minera de texto Opiniones de Apps de la Play Store

Se pide:

1.1 Carga de datos

En kaggle podis encontrar Dos ficheros cvs que contiene informacin sobre valoraciones de usuarios de apps de la Play Store y de datos sobre cada app. Descargar y documentar estos datos de Kaggle

library(tidyverse)
library(tidytext)
library(dplyr)
library(stringr)
library(wordcloud)
library(reshape2)
metadata_apps=read_csv("googleplaystore.csv")
reviews_apps=read_csv("googleplaystore_user_reviews.csv")

Limpiamos un poco los datos

reviews_apps <- reviews_apps %>% filter(Translated_Review!="nan")

# el dataset contiene muchas apps repetidas, por lo que aplico la funcin distinc,
# segun la web contiene 9660 apps nicas
metadata_apps <-
  metadata_apps %>%
  distinct(App, .keep_all = TRUE) %>%
  filter(Category!="1.9")

1.2 Anlisis descriptivo bsico

Realizar un anlisis descriptivo bsico de las tablas de opiniones y de las a caractersiticas de las apps

1.2.1 Solucin

tabla1 <- metadata_apps %>% 
  group_by(Category) %>% 
  summarise(count=n(),
            Media_Rating=round(mean(Rating,na.rm=TRUE),2),
            Median_Rating=median(Rating,na.rm=TRUE),
            Sd_Rating=sd(Rating,na.rm=TRUE),
            Max_Rating=max(Rating,na.rm=TRUE),
            Min_Rating=min(Rating,na.rm = TRUE))

  reviews_apps %>% 
  group_by(App) %>%

Top 10 de Categorias con mas reseas

top10_cat_reviews <- 
  reviews_apps %>% 
  group_by(App) %>% 
  summarise(reviews_count=n()) %>%
  inner_join(metadata_apps) %>% 
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(Category) %>% 
  summarise(reviews_cat = sum(reviews_count)) %>%
  arrange(desc(reviews_cat)) %>% 
  top_n(10)

1.3 Anlisis de sentimiento

Utilizar los tres diccionarios que hemos visto para anlisis de sentimiento y comparar con las calificaciones de los reviews que se dan en kaggle

1.3.1 Separamos las palabras de cada reviews y las reviews para cada App

tidy_reviews <- 
  reviews_apps %>%
  mutate(Review_num = row_number()) %>% 
  unnest_tokens(word, Translated_Review)

apps_review <- 
  reviews_apps %>% 
  transmute(Review_num = row_number(), App = App)

1.3.2 Usando AFINN

Agregamos una columna con el score de AFINN

reviews_sentiments <- 
  tidy_reviews %>% 
  inner_join(get_sentiments("afinn")) %>% 
  mutate(affin_score = score, score = NULL)

knitr::kable(head(reviews_sentiments))
App Sentiment Sentiment_Polarity Sentiment_Subjectivity Review_num word affin_score
10 Best Foods for You Positive 1.00 0.5333333 1 like 2
10 Best Foods for You Positive 1.00 0.5333333 1 best 3
10 Best Foods for You Positive 1.00 0.5333333 1 helps 2
10 Best Foods for You Positive 1.00 0.5333333 1 best 3
10 Best Foods for You Positive 0.25 0.2884615 2 help 2
10 Best Foods for You Positive 0.25 0.2884615 2 healthy 2

Calculamos la suma de los scores de AFINN de las review

afinn <- 
  reviews_sentiments %>% 
  group_by(Review_num) %>% 
  summarise(score_sum = sum(affin_score)) %>% 
  inner_join(apps_review)

afinn_all_apps <- 
  reviews_sentiments %>% 
  group_by(App) %>% 
  summarise(score_sum = sum(affin_score)) %>%
  mutate(method="AFINN")

Grficamos los scores de las 10 Apps con ms reviews

1.3.3 Usando BING

Agregamos una columna con el score de BING

reviews_sentiments <- 
  tidy_reviews %>% 
  inner_join(get_sentiments("bing")) %>% 
  mutate(bing_score = sentiment, sentiment = NULL)

knitr::kable(head(reviews_sentiments))

Calculamos la diferencia entre positivos y negativos de las review

bing <-
  reviews_sentiments %>% 
  group_by(Review_num) %>% 
  count(App, index = row_number(), bing_score) %>%
  spread(bing_score, n, fill = 0) %>%
  mutate(bing_score2 = positive - negative) %>%
  summarise(score_sum = sum(bing_score2)) %>%
  inner_join(apps_review)

bing_all_apps <-
  reviews_sentiments %>% 
  group_by(App) %>% 
  count(App, index = row_number(), bing_score) %>%
  spread(bing_score, n, fill = 0) %>%
  mutate(bing_score2 = positive - negative) %>%
  summarise(score_sum = sum(bing_score2)) %>%
  mutate(method="BING")

Grficamos los scores de las 10 Apps con ms reviews

1.3.4 Usando NRC

Agregamos una columna con el score de NRC

reviews_sentiments <- 
  tidy_reviews %>% 
  inner_join(get_sentiments("nrc") %>% filter(sentiment %in% c("positive", "negative"))) %>%
  mutate(nrc_score = sentiment, sentiment = NULL)

Calculamos la diferencia entre positivos y negativos de las review, similar a bing, solo filtramos los sentimientos de nrc para quedarnos con solo dos

nrc <-
  reviews_sentiments %>% 
  group_by(Review_num) %>% 
  count(App, index = row_number(), nrc_score) %>%
  spread(nrc_score, n, fill = 0) %>%
  mutate(nrc_score2 = positive - negative) %>%
  summarise(score_sum = sum(nrc_score2)) %>%
  inner_join(apps_review)

nrc_all_apps <-
  reviews_sentiments %>% 
  group_by(App) %>% 
  count(App, index = row_number(), nrc_score) %>%
  spread(nrc_score, n, fill = 0) %>%
  mutate(nrc_score2 = positive - negative) %>%
  summarise(score_sum = sum(nrc_score2)) %>%
  mutate(method="NRC")

Grficamos los scores de las 10 Apps con ms reviews

1.5 Calcular las tf-idf

Para cada tipo de aplicacin calcular las tf-idf y comparar las palabaras ms usadas

Haremos un un dataframe tidy con las reviews, la app, y la categoria de la app en una misma row.

app_categories <- 
  metadata_apps %>%
  group_by(Category) %>%
  transmute(App = App)

tidy_rev_cat <-
  tidy_reviews %>%
  inner_join(app_categories)

knitr::kable(head(tidy_rev_cat))
App Sentiment Sentiment_Polarity Sentiment_Subjectivity Review_num word Category

10 Best Foods for You Positive 1 0.5333333 1 thats HEALTH_AND_FITNESS

Ahora procedemos a remover las stopwords de las reviews

tidy_rev_cat <-
  tidy_rev_cat %>%
  anti_join(stop_words, by = c("word" = "word"))

Calcularemos la cantidad total de trminos y la frecuencia de cada uno, agrupando por categoria las apps

cat_words <- 
  tidy_rev_cat %>%
  count(Category, word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  ungroup()

total_words <- cat_words %>% 
  group_by(Category) %>% 
  summarize(total = sum(n))

all_words <- left_join(cat_words, total_words)

Ahora mostraremos un grfico de las 10 categorias con mas reviews y su distribucin de la frecuencia de trminos

Ahora procedemos a calcular la tf y idf.

tfidf_words <- all_words %>%
  bind_tf_idf(word, Category, n) %>%
  arrange(desc(tf_idf))

Visualizaremos de las 10 categorias de Apps con mas reviews sus 15 primeros terminos con mayor valor de tf_idf

Ahora mostraremos los 10 terminos mas usados de las 10 reviews mas positivas de las apps con mas reviews, usaremos los resultados anteriores de AFINN como referencia

top10_best_reviews <- afinn %>%
  filter(App %in% top10_apps_reviews$App) %>%
  group_by(App) %>%
  arrange(desc(score_sum)) %>%
  filter(row_number() <= 10)
  
best_words <- top10_best_reviews %>%
  inner_join(tidy_reviews %>% mutate(App = NULL)) %>%
  inner_join(app_categories) %>%
  inner_join(tfidf_words, by=c("word", "Category")) %>%
  group_by(App) %>%
  distinct(word, .keep_all = TRUE) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  arrange(App, desc(tf_idf)) %>%
  group_by(App) %>%
  filter(row_number() <= 10)

Ahora mostraremos los 10 terminos mas usados de las 5 reviews mas negativas de las apps con mas reviews, usaremos los resultados anteriores de AFINN como referencia

top10_worst_reviews <- afinn %>%
  filter(App %in% top10_apps_reviews$App) %>%
  group_by(App) %>%
  arrange(score_sum) %>%
  filter(row_number() <= 5)
  
worst_words <- top10_worst_reviews %>%
  inner_join(tidy_reviews %>% mutate(App = NULL)) %>%
  inner_join(app_categories) %>%
  inner_join(tfidf_words, by=c("word", "Category")) %>%
  group_by(App) %>%
  distinct(word, .keep_all = TRUE) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  arrange(App, desc(tf_idf)) %>%
  group_by(App) %>%
  filter(row_number() <= 10)
